To implement the simplified two-level system depicted in Fig. 1, three pairs of coils in the Helmholtz configuration are used to apply a 4 Gauss external magnetic field along the axis of the 493-nm (optical pumping) laser beam. This Zeeman splits the otherwise degenerate internal atomic energy levels and defines an axis of quantization of the atom. To initialize the ion to the well-defined ground state, S12,−12\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
